# Pin all text files to LF at checkout, on every platform.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS (do not remove):
# 1. lists/manifest.sha256 holds SHA-256 hashes of the list files' exact bytes.
#    With git's default autocrlf=true on Windows, JSON lists are checked out with
#    CRLF endings, every hash mismatches, and the integrity gate reports every
#    list as potentially tampered (and blocks Strike) on a fresh Windows clone.
# 2. Authenticode signatures (Sign-Module.ps1 / HardeningTomcat.cat) are equally
#    byte-sensitive: a checkout that rewrites line endings invalidates them.
# PowerShell 5.1+ runs LF-only scripts fine, so LF everywhere is safe.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.cat binary
